body:
It looks like you are trying to add a RoiAlign kernel for MLFloat16 to the CUDA EP.

There are at least three places to update for the kernel registration:
https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/blob/97659495d982982a06eee6a4e3560923b988ff7e/onnxruntime/core/providers/cuda/cuda_execution_provider.cc#L739-L740
https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/blob/97659495d982982a06eee6a4e3560923b988ff7e/onnxruntime/core/providers/cuda/cuda_execution_provider.cc#L1588-L1589
https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/blob/97659495d982982a06eee6a4e3560923b988ff7e/onnxruntime/core/providers/cuda/object_detection/roialign.cc#L72-L73

And you'll have to make sure the existing templated kernel implementation works for MLFloat16, or update it, or add another one.
https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/blob/97659495d982982a06eee6a4e3560923b988ff7e/onnxruntime/core/providers/cuda/object_detection/roialign.cc

If you provide the actual code you're building and the test script maybe we can help more.
